Give*p ear, O Shepherd of Israel, thou that leadest Joseph like a flock; thou that dwellest between the cherubims, shine forth.
Before*p Ephraim and Benjamin and Manasseh stir up thy strength, and come and save us.
Turn*p us again, O God, and cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.
O*p Lord*s God of hosts, how long wilt thou be angry against the prayer of thy people?
Thou*p feedest them with the bread of tears; and givest them tears to drink in great measure.
Thou*p makest us a strife unto our neighbours: and our enemies laugh among themselves.
Turn*p us again, O God of hosts, and cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.
Thou*p hast brought a vine out of Egypt: thou hast cast out the heathen, and planted it.
Thou*p preparedst room before it, and didst cause it to take deep root, and it filled the land.
The*p hills were covered with the shadow of it, and the boughs thereof were like the goodly cedars.
She*p sent out her boughs unto the sea, and her branches unto the river.
Why*p hast thou then broken down her hedges, so that all they which pass by the way do pluck her?
The*p boar out of the wood doth waste it, and the wild beast of the field doth devour it.
Return,*p we beseech thee, O God of hosts: look down from heaven, and behold, and visit this vine;
And*p the vineyard which thy right hand hath planted, and the branch that thou madest strong for thyself.
It*p is burned with fire, it is cut down: they perish at the rebuke of thy countenance.
Let*p thy hand be upon the man of thy right hand, upon the son of man whom thou madest strong for thyself.
So*p will not we go back from thee: quicken us, and we will call upon thy name.
Turn*p us again, O Lord*s God of hosts, cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.
